# No AI git attribution

This repository must never show an **AI coding tool** as a GitHub contributor.

## When creating commits

- **Never** add AI co-author trailers (e.g. `Co-authored-by:` lines naming an assistant).
- **Never** add `Made-with:` or similar AI attribution trailers.
- **Never** pass `--trailer` to `git commit` for AI attribution.
- Use plain commits only: `git commit -m "message"` or `-F` a message file you control.
- If attribution appears anyway, **amend locally** to remove it before push.

## When pushing

- Do not push commits whose message body contains AI co-author or Made-with trailers.
- Before the first push of new commits, verify with: `git log -1 --format=%B`.

## Author identity

- Commits should reflect the human maintainer only (e.g. Souvik Roy), not an AI agent.
